-- Togo Gets $10 Million Loan for Transport Project From Arab Bank
-- B y   S a l m a   E l   W a r d a n y
-- 2012-04-01T12:55:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-01/togo-gets-10-million-loan-for-transport-project-from-arab-bank.html
Togo signed a $10 million loan with
the Arab Bank for  Economic Development  in  Africa  for a
transportation project.  The loan will be reimbursed over a period of 30 years, and
includes a grace period of 10 years and an annual interest rate
of 10 percent, the bank said in a statement today.  The bank said its total loans to Togo reached $55.3 million
at the end of March.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Salma El Wardany in Khartoum at 
